If, says Saviguy, we look more closely into the actual contents of the first boolr of the Institutas, we find that it corresponds very nearly to what he calls family law. lt treats, in point of fact, of marriage, patria potestas, slavery, patronatus¹ guardianship (and, in Gaius, of manus aud mancipium).
